jects and implementing validation logic, though it omits some minor details like the `TARGET_FIELDS` constant and a source code comment about accessor methods being similar to the UI layer. These are non-critical omissions that don't affect the core content.\n\nFor s6, the numbered processing flow items in the source map correctly to the knowledge file's description. Looking at my findings overall, I've identified a few minor issues: two section merges in the V3 format that combine multiple RST sections without splitting despite exceeding reasonable length limits, and missing class names in the V4 hints for s5.\n\nLet me double-check the V3 rule more carefully though. For s4, the h2 content includes the XML configuration block and naming conventions, followed by two h3 sections with the request and response message format files—all combined, this definitely exceeds 2000 characters. The knowledge file does merge these together into s4. For s5, the h2 content is relatively brief, so I need to verify whether it actually triggers the splitting condition.\n\nNow I'm cross-referencing the knowledge file against the source documentation to catch any inaccuracies. Looking at s7, the text about the `onError` return behavior appears to be pulled directly from the Javadoc, so that checks out.\n\nMy key findings are narrowing down to three issues: V3 has two instances where multiple heading levels get merged into single sections without proper splitting, and V4 is missing class type hints in s5. I should verify that `ValidationContext` is actually referenced in the s5 content to confirm this is a real omission.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20381,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20381,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f221092c-1cc9-487a-b2af-0d3ed684cf1a","uuid":"271f0e